- 'Average episode reward' is the mean cumulative reward for episodes at each timestep;
- 'Maximum episode length' is the longest duration of an episode at any timestep.

- 'PPO' stands for Proximal Policy Optimization, a popular reinforcement learning algorithm;
- 'CustomEnv' is a custom environment used in reinforcement learning experiments;
- The date range '2023-01-01' to '2023-01-05' refers to the first five days of 2023.

- "Top 3" refers to the highest ranks based on the average episode reward;
- "Achieved the greatest average rewards" means having the highest average episode reward;
- "Highest peaks in a landscape of performance" is a metaphorical way to describe the top-ranking experiments and environments.

- Cumulative rewards represent the total rewards accumulated over time in a reinforcement learning experiment;
- Timesteps and episodes are discrete units of time in RL experiments;
- Agents are algorithms that interact with an environment to learn optimal behaviors;
- The 'Average Reward' metric is a performance indicator that reflects the average reward per timestep over the course of the experiment.

- 'Episode completed' in the log message refers to the completion of a specific episode in a reinforcement learning environment;
- 'INFO' log level indicates that the log entry is an informational message, typically used to report normal operations;
- 'episode_reward' is a performance metric that measures the cumulative reward obtained by the agent over a single episode.

