- Performance metrics and logs are updated regularly during and after the experiments;
- The latest performance metrics and logs provide the most current status and performance of the experiments;
- An experiment's performance metrics and logs are crucial for monitoring and evaluating the experiment's progress and outcomes.

- 'Last episode' refers to the most recent or final episode in the sequence of episodes for each experiment;
- 'Average reward' is the mean of the rewards received during the episode;
- 'Learning rate' is a hyperparameter that controls how much the model learns from each new piece of data.

- Cumulative rewards are calculated by summing the reward metrics over time for each experiment;
- The 'reward' metric is a performance metric that indicates the success or effectiveness of an experiment;
- The experiments are part of a research or development project in the field of reinforcement learning (RL).

